body.p: lists the Analog Points as they show on the screen.
The same point name is used when the point appears on the Analog Values Screen, the Event Log Screen, or the Alarms Screen.

The normal range measurement bracket for each point is given in the Low Alarm Index and High Alarm Index, which are not indexed contiguously with the point, but in adjacent tables following the list of points.
Point values may be scaled as shown in the Value Scale column. For example, for “Output %KVA A” (point 34) a 68% measurement is listed as 68, not 0.68.
Custom STSs can have different points and the standard points list may not apply.
